The Western press is convinced that Zary, a former current affairs professor at the University of Zambia in Chile, is the creator of the current Maur. But those who are close to Chama reject this facet.

For his part, Markos Harai, coordinator of the Independence Network of Friends of Zimbabwe, said in an interview: "The Zimbabwean government's policy towards Zambia has been to isolate Zambia from Eastern Africa". Isolated and even more weakened in the political process of integration of the Economic Cooperation Community (ECC), the Zairian Rur Leer collapsed.

South Africa, under the leadership of Thabo Mbeki, had an interest in keeping Zambia independent to ensure that Rur Leer did not become its base upstream of the Zambezi. Zambia contributed its weight in the Southern African Development Community.

The constant interventions by the UN Organization that suddenly saw unconstitutional actions by Kinshasa are as disturbing as the ronti.
